messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Someone was just shot and robbed.
Where did this happen?
Behind the club, Sharky's, the street beside Sharky's.
Was the person shot or are they on the ground and bleeding?
The club, he was shot, he's on the ground and bleeding.
He's by Sharky's?
Yes, the street beside Sharky's. Do you know the neighborhood Melts on us?
Okay. Is he white or black?
He's shot in the head, I can't... he looks mixed.
Can you tell me the name of the street?
Blue Street, Blue Street. I'm on Blue Street.
He's on Blue Street?
Yes, ma'am.
Where exactly on Blue Street is he laying?
Everybody is walking away and leaving him. He's laying on the ground.
Hold on, ma'am, okay?
Okay.
Have y'all found somebody?
He's dead. He's laying on the ground. He was shot. Somebody needs to help him.
What's the address?
We're on Blue Street, in the middle of the street. 9.44 Black Boulevard and Sharkey.
You're at the corner of Blue Street and Bragg Boulevard?
No, I'm in the middle of Blue Street.
Is that off Jefferson Road?
Yes, it is.
So you're not on Bragg Boulevard?
It's off Bragg Boulevard and it's on Michelin Road. They meet, and the street is in the middle of them.
Alright, I'm sending help. Can you stay on the phone with me?
I'm right by the police, by Martin Luther King. Something was just built here.
Okay. What's your telephone number?
Exactly what happened?

I don't know, sir. I was driving down the street, and these dudes stopped me. They were waving and panicking. At first I didn't stop because I was scared, but then I saw the man in the street, so I stopped. They asked me to call 911 because he was shot.
So somebody was shot?
Yes, he was shot and robbed.
Do you know the age of the patient?
No, I think he's dead, sir.
Help is being dispatched while I'm talking to you, okay?
Okay.
Is he conscious?
No, he's not.
Alright, you can hang up once you're with the police.
He told me to hang up. I'll hang up now, thank you.
Okay.
